If you're a wild blueberry harvester with a 100-acre barren, you get zip, zero, nada, zilch. If you're a cranberry farmer with a 100-acre bog, you get $61,000. How is that fair? The answer: it’s not!

Maine’s wild blueberry growers are getting hit with a double whammy – their exports to China have decreased by nearly 97% since the trade war began, AND they’ve missed out on the President’s farm bailout lottery. Even worse: no one can explain why they lost out. pic.twitter.com/pJQFIhBbIo

Maine’s wild blueberry producers have seen their exports to China drop by nearly 97%, but the Administration has left them out while providing relief for other crops.
